<!-- no particular section is absolutely required, but in general, there should
be a why, what, and how of what is being proposed -->

# Motivation

A paragraph or two of what is motivating for there to be change

# Detailed implementation / Specification (optional)

Any combination of references to pull requests, inlined code, or description
of changes which can outline the means in which the change will happened.

# Example usage (optional)

Sometimes it's best to show the impact of the changes, this can demonstrate
the value-proposition of the proposal.

# Prior art (optional)

Examples of similar discussions or implementations

# Unresolved questions (optional)

Unanswered questions with proposal, this could be things like naming, implementations,
scope, domain, second-order effects, etc.

# Future work (optional)

Items which should be done in the future. This could be: deprecation stories,
work in downstream repos, documentation, etc.

# Changes (optional)

If a specification or api, what changed over time and why

# Acknowledgements (optional)

Gratitude towards other contributors who were helpful



